text:
West 231st Street, west from Conlear Ave. to Riverdale Ave., showing W.P.A. men at work on a street and sidewalk repair job.

November 12, 1936.

Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.
title: Bronx: West 231st Street - West, Corlear to Riverdale Avenues.

text:
Irwin Avenue (bus on ramp), north from W. 231st Street, showing the concrete wall built by the W.P.A. The ramp to the left of Irwin Avenue is Riverdale Avenue, the apartment house being at the N.W. corner of W. 232nd Street. In the foreground is Spuyten Duyvil Road.

January 13, 1937

W.P.A. Photo
Five Boroughs Project
